text: Matavla () is a rural locality (a village) in Zaimkinsky Selsoviet, Duvansky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 101 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 111 km from Mesyagutovo, 4 km from Zaimka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Duvansky District
title: Matavla
